column434: Welcome to 2303 N Slater Ave, a charming 3 Bedroom, 2 Bathroom Single Family Home nestled in the heart of Compton, California. Built in 1948, this 1,090 square-foot Residence is situated on an expansive 9,555 Sqft Lot, offering ample space for outdoor activities and future expansions. As you step inside, you'll be greeted by refinished hardwood floors that flow seamlessly throughout the home. The remodeled kitchen boasts modern amenities, providing a perfect setting for culinary enthusiasts. Each bedroom offers generous space, with the master suite featuring a private bath equipped with dual sinks and its own separate entrance, ensuring privacy and convenience. The vast backyard is reminiscent of a park, presenting endless possibilities. Whether you envision expanding the existing structure or adding a second unit, this property provides the flexibility to meet your needs. Prospective buyers are encouraged to consult with the city regarding potential additions. Located in a vibrant community, this home is in proximity to several notable landmarks. The Martin Luther King, Jr. Memorial, a significant tribute to the civil rights leader, is situated within the Compton Civic Center. Additionally, the historic Heritage House, the oldest remaining house in Compton, offers a glimpse into the city's rich history.  For those seeking recreational activities, the nearby Angeles Abbey Memorial Park provides a serene environment for reflection.  Experience the perfect blend of comfort, convenience, and culture at 2303 N Slater Ave. This property is a must-see for those looking to embrace the best of Compton living.

An outstanding price - a great starter home - don't miss 1713 W Claude St, a charming single-story home nestled on a neat little residential neighborhood south of the Compton/Woodley airport and near lots of newer residential and commercial retail developments.  Easily access from the 105 freeway and centrally located in this "Hub City" that offers easy access to major freeways including the 91, 105, and 710 Freeways while at the same time providing residential neighborhoods and a strong sense of community. Built in 1949, this cozy 2- bedroom, 1-bathroom residence offers 796 sq. ft. of living space on an expansive 5,748 sq. ft. lot. Step inside to a bright and inviting living area featuring a large picture window overlooking the backyard, filling the home with natural light. The layout flows seamlessly into the kitchen, which provides direct access to the extra large backyard - great for enjoying or maybe expanding the house or adding an accessory dwelling unit.  Fruit trees offer shade and homegrown fruit, while the generous lot allows plenty of space for gardening, outdoor dining, or creating your dream retreat. With both side yard and kitchen access to the backyard, this home is designed for convenience and indoor-outdoor living.  The front yard is gated, spacious, and well-maintained, proving added privacy and security. The front yard is large enough to create your own flower or vegetable garden to complement the backyard space.Located on a quiet residential street, this home is just minutes from schools, shopping, and freeway access. With a walkability score of 78, daily errands are a breeze.Whether you're a first-time buyer, downsizing, or looking for an investment, 1713 W Claude St combines charm, functionality, and endless potential.
